<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8389609>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Maximum likelihood phylogeny analysis of the isolates SGSF303 and others based on ITS sequences. The numbers shown in the branches represent ML bootstrap support (BS) values ≥50% and Bayesian posterior probability (PP) scores ≥0.95 and show with “BS / PP”. (*) indicates type sequences." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8389609/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8389611>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Multi-gene phylogenetic analysis of the isolates SGSF303 and others based on ITS, LSU, rpb2, and tef1 sequences. The numbers shown in the branches represent ML bootstrap support (BS) values ≥50% and Bayesian posterior probability (PP) scores ≥0.95 and show with “BS / PP”." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8389611/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8389615>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Arxiella longispora. A. The front of colony in PDA. B. The reverse of colony in PDA. C. The front of colony in MEA. D. The reverse of colony in MEA. E–G. Hyphae, conidiogenous cells, and conidia. H. Conidia. Bars = 20 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8389615/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

